# SCSS conventions

- Keep selectors **component-scoped** and readable (often BEM-like: `.users-admin__grid`, etc.).
- Avoid deep nesting; nest only for pseudo states / small subtrees.
- Prefer design tokens and global utility classes from `src/styles.scss` when appropriate (CSS variables like `var(--clr-*)`, `var(--space-*)`, `var(--radius-*)`).
- Keep responsive rules close to the component block (repo pattern uses `@media` near the relevant selectors).
